@sbddesign, @HODLBarbarian, during Wednesday's BitPlebs I had asked about how the Extended Fingerprint (xfp) is derived from the Extended Public Key (xpub).  I found the answer on Bitcoin Stackexchange:

"The fingerprint of a public key is defined in BIP 32 as the first 4 bytes of the RIPEMD160 hash of the SHA256 hash of the public key. The fingerprint of a particular xpub can be gotten from that xpub"

Full answer:  https://bitcoin.stackexchange.com/questions/92534/what-is-an-extended-fingerprint-xfp-and-how-does-it-differ-from-an-xpub
